<item>
            <title>[TIKA-104] Add utility methods to throw IOException with the caused intialized</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-104</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The constructors with a Throwable cause were not added until JDK 1.6 - I suggest adding a utility method to intialize the cause in the IOException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be used to revert r596143&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; (and similar situation in AppendableApdaptor) so that the cause is not swallowed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=rev&amp;amp;revision=596143&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=rev&amp;amp;revision=596143&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
